: "dpivsoft.Examples.stereo_tutorial.u_z", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance", "documentation": ["This example test the performance of DPIV algorithm as long as the images size increase comparing\nthe processing time of python CPU and openCL implementations.\n\nThe correlation windows used are of 32x32 and 16x16 pixels in first and second pass respectively.\n\nThe correlation windows are placed in order to mantain a window overlap of 50% so that the number of\ncorrelation windows is proportional to the Image size.\n\nThe syntetic images used for the test are generated from John Howkings CFD simulation of bouyancy\ndriven mixing flow."], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.dirCode", "type": null, "documentation": ["Current path"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.dirCFD", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.dirImg", "type": null, "documentation": ["Images folder"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.CFD_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.Img_dimension", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.limits", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.factor", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.dt", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.Synt_Img.width", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.Synt_Img.height", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.dirSave", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.N_GPU", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.Performance.N_CPU", "type": null, "documentation": ["The CPU iterations are lower because CPU processing is too slow"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Examples.P