functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Cl_DPIV", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "dpivsoft.Cl_DPIV.select_Platform", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "idx", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Selection of the device to run opencl calculations.\n\nidx: identifier int of platform in the computer.\n\nif idx is a string called \"selection\", the terminal shows a list\nof all available platforms in the computer to select one."]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Cl_DPIV.compile_Kernels", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "thr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Compiles all kernels needed for GPU calculation.\nOnly needs to be called once.\n\nKernels are by default in relative the path: ./GPU_Kernels."]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Cl_DPIV.initialization", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "width", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "height", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "thr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Initialize variables in GPU memory"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Cl_DPIV.processing", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "img1_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "img2_name", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "thr", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Perform a parallelized 2 pass PIV algorithm with window deformation\nexecuted on openCL.\n\nDeveloped by Jorge Aguilar-Cabello\n\nInputs:\n-------\nImg1_name: str\n    Path to the first Image of the next iteration to be loaded\n    asynchronously during runtime\n\nImg2_name: str\n    Path to the second Image of the next iteration to be loaded\n    asynchronously during runtime\n\nthr: openCL object\n    Platform where to perform the operations in openCL.\n\nParameters: class\n    Saved in  \"Classes.py\" file. It contains all PIV procesing parameters\n    to be used in calculations. Parameters can be changed manually or\n    loaded from external file by using the classmethod: \"readParameters\".\n    Use $help class for more information about PIV parameters.\n\nOutputs:\n--------\nGPU: Class\n    Saved in \"Classes.py\". Containing all data stored in GPU memory.\n    Following outputs are all included inside this class.\n\ngx1: GPU 2d array\n    x meshgrid on GPU from first sweep.\n\ngx2: GPU 2d array\n    x meshgrid on GPU from second sweep.\n\ngy1: GPU 2d array\n    y meshgrid on GPU from first sweep.\n\ngy2: GPU 2d array\n    y meshgrid on GPU from second sweep.\n\ngu1: GPU 2d array\n    velocity field in x direction on GPU from first sweep\n\ngu2: GPU 2d array\n    velocity field in x direction on GPU from second sweep\n\ngv1: GPU 2d array\n    velocity field in y direction on GPU from first sweep\n\ngv2: GPU 2d array\n    velocity field in y direction on GPU from second sweep"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Classes", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Parameters", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Parameters.readParameters", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fileName", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Read parameters from a yaml file"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Parameters.introParameters", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Introduce a parameter manually, not implemented yet (probably\nneeded for a GUI)"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Parameters.box_size_1_x", "type": null, "documentation": ["Cross-correlation box1"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Parameters.box_size_1_y", "type": null, "documentation": ["Cross-correlation box1"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Parameters.no_boxes_1_x", "type": null, "documentation": ["Number of x-windows"]}, {"name": "dpivsoft.Classes.Paramet